problem link: https://leetcode.com/problems/subarray-sum-equals-k/description/

Intuition
In this problem the main thing to understand is that we want to know at any index i , the total of that subarray is current prefix sum , so we want to know is there a previous prefix sum whose sum is total - k , then the elements between the earlier position and current index must be equal to k.

meaning current_prefix sum - previous_prefix sum = k

at every index we know current prefix sum is total sum of that subarray
suppose there was an earlier prefix sum equal to total - k , then: total - (total -k) = k, which means the element between those two prefix sum form a subarray with sum = k, therefore for every index we simply need to know how many times the prefix sum total - k has occured , a hashmap allows us to track these frequencies effectifely , the hashmap as a database of all prefix sums seen so far.

Approach
step 1 create an empty hash map f which help us in tracking if we have seen total - k before , initally f[0] = 1 , as sum of an empty subarray is 0 , total = 0 which we will need to calaculate the current prefix sum of subarray , count to keep track of the frequencies of total - k

loop condition from start to end of array
update total at every index
ask question is there total - k in hash map
freq = frequency of question in hashmap , if it exsists it will return else it will return zero ,
update count by the freq
update hash map with total

return count

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(n)

Code
class Solution:
    def subarraySum(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:
        total = count = 0
        f = {}
        f[0] = 1
        
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            total += nums[i]
            ques = total - k
            freq = f.get(ques,0)
            count += freq
            f[total] = f.get(total,0) + 1
        return count 
